pageTitle: Prom fashion show highlights affordable fashions | SpencerMagnet.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {32755=Copyright © 2015, 24938=The Spencer Magnet | circulation@spencermagnet.com | 502-477-2239 P.O. Box 219, 100 W Main Street, Taylorsville, KY 40071 Office Hours are 9:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m., Monday through Friday, 19189=The Spencer County Family Resource and Youth Service Center sponsored the annual Prom Fashion Show on March 8 at the high school. Fashions were auctioned off at a fraction of the price, making prom more accessible for some students. Students had the opportunity to sign the SCHS 2012 prom pledge, which read: “I want my prom to be a night I’ll remember for the rest of my life — surrounded by my best friends and full of music, dancing and fun. I don’t want anything to get in the way of these memories.}
